    <div class="intro">
      <h1 action="/intro" method="post">Title: Aadhaar-Based Alcohol Purchase Management System</h1>
      <h3>
        •The Aadhaar-Based Alcohol Purchase Management System is a web-based application developed to make alcohol sales
        more secure, transparent, and responsible. In this system, every customer must register and verify their
        identity using their Aadhaar number before purchasing alcohol. The Aadhaar number acts as a unique identifier,
        helping prevent duplicate records and maintain an accurate purchase history. <br><br>

        •The system records each customer's purchase details, including the Aadhaar number, brand name, price, date, and
        time. It also enforces a rule that each customer can purchase only one bottle of alcohol per week. If a customer
        has already purchased a bottle during the current week, the system automatically denies any additional purchase
        until the following week.<br><br>

        •This project helps promote responsible alcohol distribution, reduces excessive purchases, maintains a reliable
        purchase history through Aadhaar verification, and provides a secure and efficient digital solution for alcohol
        sales management. It also enables authorized users to manage customer records and purchase details in an
        organized manner.<br><br>

        •Technologies Used:<br>

        Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript<br>
        Backend: Node.js, Express.js<br>
        Database: MongoDB<br>
        Template Engine: EJS <br>
      </h3>
    </div><br>
    <div  class="intro">
      <h1>Adventage of the Projects  </h1>
      <h3>
        • Helps families verify whether a person consumed alcohol before marriage .<br>
        • Limits each customer to purchasing only one bottle per week. <br>
        • Prevents underage alcohol purchases through Aadhaar verification.<br>
        • Helps reduce alcohol addiction by controlling frequent purchases.<br>
        • Maintains a digital record of every customer's purchase history.<br>
        • Restricts alcohol purchases for people below the eligible age.<br>
        • Reduces fake identities and duplicate purchases.<br>
        • Helps shopkeepers follow government rules more effectively.<br>
        • Saves time through automated customer verification and record management.<br>
        • Increases transparency and accountability in alcohol sales.<br>
      </h3>
    </div>
